  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing Community Preparedness in Davao Oriental</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In its current phase, the project is increasing the disaster preparedness and response capability of 12 vulnerable barangays in Typhoon Bopha-affected coastal municipalities of Baganga, Cateel and Boston municipalities of Davao Oriental. By focusing on enhancing the disaster risk reduction and management (DRRM) capacities of local government units (LGUs) at the barangay and municipal levels, the current project is enhancing the resilience of the target barangays through community and school-based DRRM interventions. Now on its second phase, the project is employing similar approaches and have expanded the geographic scope, impact, and achievement of the project&apos;s objectives to 16 new barangays, including a new municipality Caraga. As in the project&apos;s first phase, the targeted barangays are still recovering from the impacts of Typhoon Bopha, remain highly vulnerable to the impacts of natural disasters (as the effects of the recent Tropical Depression Agaton&#x9D; demonstrated), and do not have functioning Barangay Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Councils (BDRRMC). The expansion phase will enable the project to nearly double the preparedness and response capacities among localities and their vulnerable groups, introducing these benefits to an expansion municipality (Caraga), and strengthen partnerships with local government units and community organizations in Davao Oriental.</narrative>
  </description>
